Keywords:
Dementia
Incretin-based
 therapy
Systematic
 review
a
 b  s
 t  r  a  c  t
We  performed
 a
 PRISMA
 systematic
 review
 of
 incretin-based
 therapies
 and
 effects
 on
 neu-
rocognitive
 function
 in
 humans.
 There
 was
 observational
 evidence
 to
 support
 dipeptidyl
peptidase-IV
 inhibitors
 in
 improving
 cognition,
 whilst
 glucagon-like
 peptide-1
 had
 positive
effects
 on
 cerebral
 glucose
 metabolism.
 Powered
 clinical
 trials
 are
 now
 needed
 in
 patients
with-
 and
 without
 diabetes.
